        "body": "<p>You can look at the difference between the two files using <code>jar tf<\/code> followed by the archive. It may be that one of the archives is including the signed content, which will mean that upon load, the JVM will verify that the content is the same. You could perhaps see if there is a similar execution time when running with <code>-Xverify:none<\/code>, although I'd recommend against doing that in a production system.<\/p>\n",
